Confirmed the defect with a focused regression test in [tests/test_requests.py](/workspace/repo/tests/test_requests.py:978).

`pytest -q tests/test_requests.py -k invalid_ssl_certificate_files` fails because `HTTPAdapter.cert_verify` raises plain `OSError` for `/garbage`, not `FileNotFoundError`.

The test now requires:

- `FileNotFoundError`
- `errno == errno.ENOENT`
- `filename == "/garbage"`

No production code was changed.
